# Smoky Sloppy Sauce

Prep Time: 5 minutes  
Cooking Time: 15 minutes  
Total Time: 20 minutes

*enough sauce for 1 lb of ground meat or non-meat equivalent*

* 1 tbsp avocado oil (or other neutral oil)
* 1/2 orange or red bell pepper, diced
* 15 oz tomato sauce
* 2 tbsp brown sugar
* 1 tsp chipotle powder
* 1 tsp chili powder
* 1/4 tsp smoked paprika
* 1 tsp roasted garlic powder
* 2 tsp ground cumin
* fine salt and pepper, to taste

1. In a deep skillet or dutch oven, heat oil on medium heat.
2. Add peppers. Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
3. Add tomato sauce and remainder of ingredients. Mix well. Reduce heat to low, cook five minutes.
4. Add meat/meat-equivalent to sauce and cook five more minutes, or refrigerate sauce and use within 4-5 days.

Adapted from [The Minimalist Baker](https://minimalistbaker.com/vegan-sloppy-joes)


